default&#xa0;default2. defaultNew and innovative responses to the changes to housing support default&#xa0;
defaultMutual Exchange
default&#xa0;
default2.1
default 
defaultCircle 
defaultHousing Group provides House Exchange, the country’s largest not-for-profit web-based mutual exchange service. 
defaultHouse Exchange allows for home swaps between 
defaultany council and housing association tenant with the right to mutually exchange by
default automatically matc
defaulthing house-seekers with 
defaulta home
default that meet their needs. There are 300,000 people registered on the site and more than 220,000 properties on the system.
default&#xa0;
default2.2 Mutual exchange can be a useful tool in responding to welfare reform by enabling tenants to move to a
default property which is cheaper to run or which has fewer bedrooms 
defaultand therefore avoids the Under-O
defaultccupation Penalty.
default&#xa0;
default2.3
default Indeed, since the Under-O
defaultccupation Penalty was introduced in April 2013, the number of registrations to House Exchange website, 
defaultwww.houseexchange.org.uk
default, have increased by 26%. The majority of those registering on the site, around 26%, are looking to move to a larger property 
defaultbut 
defaultthe number looking to down
default-size
default has increased as a proportion of registrations to around 10%.
default We have also held 
defaultsuccessful ‘speed-dating’ events where we invite
default tenants 
defaultto attend and try to 
defaultfind a 
defaultsuitable 
defaultproperty match for mutual exchange.
